In a small #pot{}, combine @jasmine rice{3/4%cup}, @water{1 1/4%cups}, and a big pinch of @salt{}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

Wash and dry produce.

Halve, core, and thinly slice @bell pepper{1} into strips. Halve, peel, and thinly slice @yellow onion{1}. Zest and quarter @lime{1}.

Open and drain @tofu{1}; press out excess water with #paper towels{}. Crumble tofu into pea-size pieces over a #medium bowl{}.

Heat a large drizzle of @cooking oil{8%tsp} in large, preferably nonstick, pan over medium-high heat. Add bell pepper and onion; season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook, stirring, until tender and lightly browned, ~{6-9%minutes}.

> If veggies begin to brown too quickly, add a few splashes of water and continue cooking until liquid has evaporated.

Transfer veggies to a #plate{}.

Heat 2 TBSP oil in same #pan{} over medium-high heat. Once oil is hot, add tofu and spread out in an even layer. Cook undisturbed until lightly browned on the bottom, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Stir, then cook until lightly browned all over, ~{1-2%minutes} more.

Turn off heat. Add veggies, @soy sauce{2%tbsp}, @mushroom stock concentrate{1}, @sweet soy glaze{4%tbsp}, @sweet Thai chili sauce{1%oz}, and a squeeze of lime juice. Stir until tofu mixture is thoroughly coated.

Fluff rice with #fork{} and stir in lime zest to taste. Season with salt and pepper if desired.

Roughly chop @peanuts{1%oz}. Finely chop @cilantro{1/4%ounce}.

Divide rice between #bowls{}. Top with tofu and veggies, peanuts, and cilantro. Serve with remaining lime wedges on the side.